                                                                              "message":  "Based on the latest information available from the X posts and related web results, here\u0027s an update on the performance metrics comparison between DeepSeek\u0027s models and OpenAI\u0027s:\n\n- **DeepSeek LLM 67B Chat**: This model has shown exceptional performance on never-before-seen exams, particularly the Hungarian National High-School Exam, where it was evaluated for mathematical capabilities. It scored highly, demonstrating its proficiency in handling complex problems. Additionally, it exhibits outstanding performance in coding (HumanEval Pass@1: 73.78) and mathematics (GSM8K 0-shot: 84.1, Math 0-shot: 32.6).[](https://github.com/deepseek-ai/DeepSeek-LLM)\n\n- **DeepSeek-R1**: This model consistently outperforms or matches OpenAI-o1 across most benchmarks. Notably, it scored 79.8% on AIME 2024 and 49.2% on SWE-bench Verified, indicating high adaptability and scalability. The DeepSeek-R1–32B variant also achieves competitive performance with fewer computational resources, suggesting efficiency in scaling.[](https://medium.com/data-science-in-your-pocket/deepseek-r1-best-open-source-reasoning-llm-outperforms-openai-o1-b79869392945)\n\n- **DeepSeek-V3**: This version is noted for outperforming Llama 3.1 405B and GPT-4o on key benchmarks. It achieved 48.5% accuracy on Polyglot, which tests code generation in multiple languages, beating Claude Sonnet 3.5 but not o1. In language tasks, it performed comparably to Claude 3.5 Sonnet. DeepSeek-V3 was trained with significantly less time and cost than Llama 3.1 405B, which it substantially outperforms.[](https://www.deeplearning.ai/the-batch/deepseek-v3-redefines-llm-performance-and-cost-efficiency/)\n\n- **General Comparison**: DeepSeek models are highlighted for their ability to perform well across diverse benchmarks, indicating their versatility in various tasks. They have shown to be competitive or superior in terms of performance, adaptability, and cost efficiency compared to OpenAI\u0027s models. The open-source nature of DeepSeek\u0027s models provides an advantage in terms of evaluation, allowing for direct token-level comparison which is not possible with OpenAI\u0027s closed-source models.[](https://data-ai.theodo.com/blog-technique/open-source-llms-vs-openai)\n\nThese insights suggest that DeepSeek\u0027s latest models are not just competitive but in many areas, they are setting new standards in the field of large language models, both in terms of performance metrics and resource efficiency.",
